cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper proposes a computational model for rapid learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The model leverages information from long-term memory, which involves cognitive processes and could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach aims to improve the learning task of input from sensory memory, which could involve neural networks and could be categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The proposed method is applied to supervised classifications, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL).
